\noindent \hspace{1em}Give your answer as a fraction in its simplest form.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\item Another 320 cars cross the bridge.

\noindent \hspace{1em}How many of these 320 cars are expected to be white?

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\item Heidi also records the number of people in each car crossing the bridge for one hour.

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{|c|c|}
\hline
Number of people & Frequency \\
\hline
1 & 20 \\
2 & 6 \\
3 & 0 \\
4 & 15 \\
5 & 8 \\
6 & 12 \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\noindent \hspace{1em}Calculate the mean.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{3}

